article.headline: Fla Atlantic 95, Campbell 80
article.story: BOCA RATON, Fla. (AP) -- Earnest Crumbley scored 39 points to become Florida Atlantic's all-time leading scorer and help his team snap a nine-game losing streak by beating Campbell 95-80 on Thursday night. Crumbley was 12-of-22 from the field -- including an 11-for-18 effort from 3-point range -- and pushed his career scoring total to 1,525 points, 24 more than Craig Buchanan totaled for the Owls from 1993-97. Mike Bell and Jeff Cowans each scored 14 points for Florida Atlantic (9-17, 6-13), which clinched the eighth and final spot in the Atlantic Sun Conference tournament. Bell and Robert Williams each had nine rebounds for the winners, who held a 49-37 rebounding edge. Corey Parker had 24 points for Campbell (3-22, 3-16). Anthony Atkinson had 16 points and Diego Aguiar scored 10 for the Fighting Camels. Florida Atlantic trailed 32-31 late in the first half, but a 23-4 burst over a five-minute stretch gave the Owls a sizable cushion and they kept at least a double-digit lead the rest of the way. The lead was 45-34 by halftime, and the Owls quickly put the game out of reach. Bell hit a 3-pointer 10 seconds into the second half, then Crumbley scored six points within a 36-second span to push the margin to 54-36 with 18:24 remaining. As a team, Florida Atlantic was 18-for-39 from 3-point range.
